Tho instrument of the public or Festal Paean was at first, as was to be expected, the lyre‚ and later flute and lyre, or even, notably in the Processional Paean, the flute alone. The accompaniment of the Symposiac Paean, as we have seen, was given by the flute.

The Paeans both Festa] and Symposiac were turned 10 secular use before the end of the 4th Century. The Encomium or EULOGY was the result of a similar but far earlier change.
